{"questionId":"17561","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>M-Line is a company that prints and sells custom designs on T-shirts. For each order, they&nbsp;charge an initial design fee and then an additional fee for each printed T-shirt.</p>\n<p>M-Line charges <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"M\">\n  <mi>M</mi>\n</math></span> euros per order. This charge is modelled by the linear function <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"M\\left( x \\right) = 5x + 40\">\n  <mi>M</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>40</mn>\n</math></span>, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> is the number of T-shirts in the order.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the initial design fee charged for each order.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"40\"> <mn>40</mn> </math></span> (euros)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)&nbsp; (C1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17561","referenceCode":"19N.1.SL.TZ0.T_2a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the initial design fee charged for each order.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}